<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl text-stone-900 dark:text-stone-100 mb-6">Upload Guide</h1>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200 mb-4">What Specimen Gallery Accepts</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-4">
      Specimen Gallery is a public, open collection of specimen images intended for education, research, and illustration.
    </p>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-2">We prioritize images that are:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 ml-4">
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>Clear and high quality</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>Focused on a single specimen</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>Suitable for reuse in scientific and educational contexts</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200 mb-4">Image Ownership & Licensing</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-3">Please only upload images that you:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 ml-4 mb-4">
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>Created yourself, or</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>Have the legal right to share under an open license</span>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-3">We support the following licenses:</p>
    <div class="space-y-4 mb-4">
      <div class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 font-mono text-sm bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700 text-stone-700 dark:text-stone-300 px-2 py-1 rounded h-fit">CC0</span>
        <div>
          <p class="font-medium text-stone-700 dark:text-stone-300">Public Domain</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">You waive copyright and allow anyone to use the image freely, without attribution.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 font-mono text-sm bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700 text-stone-700 dark:text-stone-300 px-2 py-1 rounded h-fit">CC-BY</span>
        <div>
          <p class="font-medium text-stone-700 dark:text-stone-300">Attribution Required</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400">Others may use the image freely, but must credit the creator.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200 mb-4">About Stock Images</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-3">
      Stock images (for example from free photo websites) may be used only if their license is compatible with CC-BY and proper attribution is provided.
    </p>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-3">
      However, for long-term scientific and educational use, we strongly encourage original photographs and observations whenever possible.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200 mb-4">Image Quality Guidelines</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-3">For best results:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 ml-4 mb-4">
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>One specimen per image</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>Minimal background or clean cutout</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>PNG or WebP preferred</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>Minimum resolution of 512 × 512 pixels</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
      Images do not need to be perfectly isolated — clarity is more important than perfection.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200 mb-4">Scientific Naming</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-3">
      When uploading, please provide the most accurate scientific name you can.
    </p>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-2">If you are unsure:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-1 text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 ml-4 mb-3">
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>Use the suggested taxonomy results</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">•</span>
        <span>Or submit the image for review</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
      Community and curator review helps improve accuracy over time.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10 p-6 bg-stone-100 dark:bg-stone-800 rounded-xl">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 dark:text-stone-200 mb-3">Our Goal</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300 mb-2">
      Specimen Gallery exists to create a clear, reusable visual reference of the natural world.
    </p>
    <p class="text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
      Thoughtful contributions help ensure the collection remains useful for everyone.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="pt-6 border-t border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-700">
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 dark:text-stone-400">
      Ready to contribute? <%= link_to "Upload a specimen", new_specimen_asset_path, class: "text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500 hover:underline" %>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

